5000|$|Intelligence sources {{claimed as}} early as 2008 that Zubaydah had been <b>waterboarded</b> no less than ten times {{in the span of}} one week. Zubaydah was <b>waterboarded</b> 83 times within the month of August 2002, the month the CIA was {{authorized}} to use this enhanced interrogation techniques for him. In January 2010, Kiriakou, in a memoir, said, [...] "Now we know that Zubaydah was <b>waterboarded</b> eighty-three times in a single month, raising questions about how much useful information he actually supplied." ...|$|R
