25|$|The Khmer Rouge at the Tuol Sleng {{prison in}} Phnom Penh, Cambodia, used <b>waterboarding</b> {{as a method}} of torture between 1975 and 1979. The {{practice}} was perfected by Duch's lieutenants Mam Nai and Tang Sin Hean and documented in a painting by former inmate Vann Nath, which is on display in the Tuol Sleng Genocide Museum. The museum also has on display boards and other actual tools used for <b>waterboarding</b> during the Khmer Rouge regime.|$|E
